Steps to Installing Git on Linux OS :

1)Install Git using apt -get command
	sudo apt -get install git

2) Verify Installation 
	git --verssion / --v

3)Configure your git username and email 
	git config --global user.name "username"
	git config --global user.email "useremailaddress"
	
	this global indicates that you have intsall git globally, 
	it means from any location(directory /folder) you allow to use git cmmds.
